           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-4">Kan-at, Gho Thgalā, Tai Kaṁ Vraḥ, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Phtal, Tai Saṁ-ap, Tai Vraḥ Śrīya, Tai <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied> called Paṁnaṅ, <gap reason="lost"/>, 4 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 6 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, a baby boy; grand total 12.</p>
              <p n="4-34"><gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kanhyaṅ, Tai <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by her sons <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied> named Kansip, Kan<gap reason="lost"/>, <gap reason="lost"/>, <gap reason="lost"/> Adan, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/> Kanteṅ, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, <supplied reason="subaudible">Gho</supplied> <gap reason="lost"/>khasiva, <gap reason="lost"/>, <gap reason="lost"/> khānta, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, another <supplied reason="subaudible">Gho</supplied> Kansip, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>,Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, another Gho <gap reason="lost"/>,Gho Śaśīndra, <gap reason="lost"/>, another Gho Kansip, Gho Kanteṅ, Gho Śūnyavyāpi, Gho Chke, Gho Kamalaruci, <gap reason="lost"/>, another Gho Kansip, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, another Gho Kaṁpañ, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kaṁpañ, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Vaktraśiva, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Paṇdan, <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, <supplied reason="subaudible">Gho</supplied> <gap reason="lost"/>śiva, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, another <supplied reason="subaudible">Gho</supplied> Kaṁpañ, <gap reason="lost"/> 5 <gap reason="lost"/>, <gap reason="lost"/> children.</p>
              
